YELLOW FEVER - AMERICAS (10): BRAZIL
************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 30 Jan 2018 17h11 BRST
Source: Secretariat of Health Surveillance, Ministry of Health [in Portuguese trans. Mod.TY, edited]
http://portalms.saude.gov.br/noticias/agencia-saude/42422-ministerio-da-saude-atualiza-casos-de-febre-amarela-30-jan


This [Tue 30 Jan 2018], the Ministry of Health updated the information sent from the state secretariats of health about the yellow fever situation in the country. During the monitoring period (from 1 Jul 2017-30 Jan 2018), 213 yellow fever cases were confirmed in the country, including 81 deaths. In total, 1080 suspected cases were notified of which 432 were discarded and 435 remain under investigation.

Last year [2017] from July 2016 to 30 Jan 2017 there were 468 confirmed cases with 147 confirmed deaths. Since last year [2017], the yellow fever reports continue [indicating] seasonality of the disease, showing most cases in summer. Given this, the period for analysis is considered as 1 Jul- 30 Jun each year.

The Ministry of Health, in 2017 to present, has sent to the Federal Units [states and the Federal District] approximately 58.9 million doses of the vaccine. For the states of São Paulo, Minas Gerais, Rio de Janeiro, Espírito Santo, and Bahia, about 49.8 million doses were sent with the objective of intensifying the vaccination strategies, with: 19.7 million for [São Paulo] , 10.7 million [Minas Gerais], 12 million (RJ), 3.7 million [Espírito Santo], and 37 million [Bahia].

