[The data above clearly indicate that the confirmed yellow fever cases and deaths during this outbreak have occurred in 3 states and the Federal District. Of these states 2, São Paulo, and Rio de Janeiro, contain Brazil's most populace cities. So far, all human cases are due to spill-over from the sylvan (forest) cycle of transmission with no indication of cases due to the urban, _Aedes aegypti_ cycle. However, there is a significant risk for these 2 cities since the _A. aegypti_ mosquito vectors are present there. The vaccination campaigns are very ambitious but urgent, since new cases continue to occur there, with ongoing evidence of nearby circulation of the virus in the sylvan (forest) cycle of transmission. The vaccination campaign is an effort to prevent that sylvan-urban spill-over from happening.

Maps of Brazil: http://s13.postimg.org/jumnalk87/map_of_Brazil.gif and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5597486,6. - Mod.TY]
